        "In “Stairway,” the acoustic guitar is not just one performance—multiple takes are stacked for shimmer, especially in the early verses.",
        "In “Jingo” by Santana, percussion is stacked: congas, timbales, shakers, and hand percussion all recorded as separate tracks, creating a dense rhythmic surface."
